2
00:00:41,230 --> 00:00:42,370
Good morning.

3
00:00:43,670 --> 00:00:46,320
It's Wednesday, 28th February.

4
00:00:47,130 --> 00:00:49,130
How's your morning today?

5
00:00:51,370 --> 00:00:55,930
This year, 2024, is a leap year.

6
00:00:57,100 --> 00:01:00,330
Tomorrow is a day that comes only once every four years,

7
00:01:00,490 --> 00:01:02,070
29th February.

8
00:01:04,270 --> 00:01:08,600
A leap year has 366 days.

9
00:01:08,800 --> 00:01:11,270
That's very special, isn't it?

10
00:01:12,400 --> 00:01:14,200
By the way,

11
00:01:14,300 --> 00:01:18,460
do you know why we have leap years?

12
00:01:19,660 --> 00:01:21,730
Because the earth orbits around the sun...

13
00:01:21,730 --> 00:01:22,700
Minato.

14
00:01:24,360 --> 00:01:25,330
Minato.

15
00:01:30,210 --> 00:01:31,640
You scared me.

16
00:01:31,760 --> 00:01:33,390
I thought you were dead.

17
00:01:33,430 --> 00:01:35,010
You have to stop doing this.

18
00:01:43,340 --> 00:01:44,950
- Here.
- Thank you.

19
00:01:47,850 --> 00:01:49,110
It still works?

20
00:01:49,840 --> 00:01:50,860
Yeah.

21
00:01:51,850 --> 00:01:53,640
It's surprisingly durable.

22
00:01:55,800 --> 00:01:57,860
What's on that MD you're listening to?

23
00:01:59,220 --> 00:02:00,680
It's an old song I wrote.

24
00:02:03,470 --> 00:02:06,100
The song about your first love?

25
00:02:06,100 --> 00:02:09,470
A special day that only comes around once every four years.

26
00:02:09,770 --> 00:02:11,560
How are you planning to spend it?

27
00:02:16,600 --> 00:02:18,010
Hey, Himari.

28
00:02:18,850 --> 00:02:19,890
What's wrong?

29
00:02:19,900 --> 00:02:21,140
Stop following me.

30
00:02:22,260 --> 00:02:23,740
Why are you crying?

31
00:02:23,780 --> 00:02:25,530
It's got nothing to do with you, Kotaro.

32
00:02:26,110 --> 00:02:28,910
You used to tell me everything.

33
00:02:30,730 --> 00:02:32,600
C'mon. Tell me.

34
00:02:34,630 --> 00:02:36,370
We're not kids anymore.

35
00:02:37,340 --> 00:02:38,470
Leave me alone.

36
00:02:42,470 --> 00:02:43,520
What's with her?

37
00:02:47,780 --> 00:02:49,330
Hey, Mom!

38
00:02:50,360 --> 00:02:51,850
Welcome back, Himari.

39
00:02:51,860 --> 00:02:52,810
Welcome back.

40
00:02:52,940 --> 00:02:53,870
You're early.

41
00:02:54,410 --> 00:02:55,870
Oh. You're here too, Dad.

42
00:02:56,170 --> 00:02:57,770
Hey, what...

43
00:02:58,050 --> 00:02:59,600
I can't be here?

44
00:02:59,640 --> 00:03:01,760
Stop that.

45
00:03:07,780 --> 00:03:08,770
Smells good.

46
00:03:10,490 --> 00:03:12,300
It's Mom's favourite flower, isn't it?

47
00:03:12,410 --> 00:03:13,070
That's right.

48
00:03:13,160 --> 00:03:15,060
Your dad got them for me.

49
00:03:17,500 --> 00:03:19,540
Is that... a birthday present?

50
00:03:20,480 --> 00:03:23,000
Tomorrow is Mom's first birthday in four years!

51
00:03:23,010 --> 00:03:24,650
Yeah, four years.

52
00:03:25,060 --> 00:03:28,020
Mom's birthday

53
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:29,280
Tomorrow, Mom will finally turn...

54
00:03:29,550 --> 00:03:30,860
Nine!

55
00:03:32,300 --> 00:03:35,100
Well, even if my birthday is only every four years,

56
00:03:35,170 --> 00:03:37,650
I still get older every year, don't I?

57
00:03:38,760 --> 00:03:40,020
That's true.

58
00:03:45,260 --> 00:03:47,270
Kayoda-san, you have a minute?

59
00:03:47,790 --> 00:03:48,500
Sure.

60
00:03:58,060 --> 00:03:58,950
Himari.

61
00:04:03,170 --> 00:04:03,970
What is it?

62
00:04:04,860 --> 00:04:05,930
Did something happen?

63
00:04:09,080 --> 00:04:10,250
Nothing.

64
00:04:10,390 --> 00:04:11,260
Hmm?

65
00:04:11,890 --> 00:04:14,230
Did you have a fight with Kotaro-kun?

66
00:04:16,310 --> 00:04:18,110
It's got nothing to do with Kotaro.

67
00:04:18,740 --> 00:04:22,220
He's just a childhood friend who butts his nose into everything.

68
00:04:32,320 --> 00:04:33,780
The boy that I like.

69
00:04:38,250 --> 00:04:39,800
He has a girlfriend.

70
00:04:41,870 --> 00:04:43,520
You mentioned him before.

71
00:04:43,670 --> 00:04:44,920
He's a senior at school?

72
00:04:49,160 --> 00:04:51,450
I wish I hadn't fallen for him.

73
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:00,810
Falling in love...

74
00:05:01,490 --> 00:05:03,330
Finding someone that you like.

75
00:05:03,690 --> 00:05:06,260
Is a really beautiful thing.

76
00:05:12,290 --> 00:05:13,650
But when you fall in love.

77
00:05:15,770 --> 00:05:17,810
It's nothing but pain.

78
00:05:25,750 --> 00:05:26,780
Hey, Himari.

79
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:29,370
I need you to do something for me.

80
00:05:55,700 --> 00:05:56,700
Himari!

81
00:05:59,270 --> 00:06:00,760
What are you doing?

82
00:06:01,250 --> 00:06:03,780
Mom asked me to bring her this box.

83
00:06:24,290 --> 00:06:26,350
Himari, come with me.

84
00:06:31,120 --> 00:06:32,790
Today the doctor said,

85
00:06:34,770 --> 00:06:36,370
to be prepared.

86
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:41,900
But Mom looks fine.

87
00:06:47,900 --> 00:06:50,320
When she moved from the hospital to this facility,

88
00:06:51,130 --> 00:06:53,270
they said she might not make it to her birthday.

89
00:06:53,270 --> 00:06:54,310
Do you remember?

90
00:07:02,240 --> 00:07:03,270
But Mom,

91
00:07:03,900 --> 00:07:05,200
really hung in there.

92
00:07:07,730 --> 00:07:09,670
Even though it must have been so tough on her.

93
00:07:10,780 --> 00:07:12,130
She's always smiling

94
00:07:18,260 --> 00:07:18,970
That's why.

95
00:07:20,060 --> 00:07:21,470
For her birthday tomorrow.

96
00:07:22,090 --> 00:07:24,070
Let's make it extra special for her.

97
00:07:32,800 --> 00:07:33,600
Himari.

98
00:07:35,380 --> 00:07:36,470
I have a favour to ask.

99
00:07:37,530 --> 00:07:38,330
What is it?

100
00:08:01,170 --> 00:08:02,570
Go to Tokyo.

101
00:08:03,330 --> 00:08:04,470
Find this man.

102
00:08:06,180 --> 00:08:07,800
And give that to him.

103
00:08:29,450 --> 00:08:42,130
366 Days

104
00:09:01,350 --> 00:09:07,110
Okinawa

105
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:10,180
Luckily you didn't break it.

106
00:09:10,530 --> 00:09:13,180
They said it'll be two weeks before the cast can come off.

107
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:15,160
You should stop riding that scooter.

108
00:09:15,350 --> 00:09:16,730
Ride a bike instead.

109
00:09:16,860 --> 00:09:19,130
No way. Bicycles are so lame.

110
00:09:19,300 --> 00:09:21,470
That helmet is even lamer.

111
00:09:22,200 --> 00:09:23,070
Lame how?

112
00:09:23,170 --> 00:09:23,500
Lame.

113
00:09:23,500 --> 00:09:24,870
Kayoda-san.

114
00:09:24,870 --> 00:09:26,480
Kayoda Ryusei-san.

115
00:09:26,480 --> 00:09:27,370
Here!

116
00:09:28,260 --> 00:09:30,070
Oh, sorry, can you hold this?

117
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:32,710
Oh, c'mon...

118
00:09:36,230 --> 00:09:37,250
I'm so sorry.

119
00:09:43,670 --> 00:09:44,570
Ah.

120
00:09:51,760 --> 00:09:53,830
Um, ah, that's actually my...

121
00:10:10,100 --> 00:10:12,370
That was Minato-senpai, right?

122
00:10:12,970 --> 00:10:14,490
You know him, Ryusei?

123
00:10:14,610 --> 00:10:16,500
He's in third year at our school.

124
00:10:16,500 --> 00:10:18,600
He was kendo club captain.

125
00:10:19,530 --> 00:10:21,870
Good looking, smart, respected.

126
00:10:21,970 --> 00:10:23,130
Miu, you don't know him?

127
00:10:23,790 --> 00:10:24,490
Nope.

128
00:10:25,190 --> 00:10:26,710
His mom got sick.

129
00:10:26,710 --> 00:10:28,130
And he quit club activities.

130
00:10:29,370 --> 00:10:31,130
He lost his father in an accident.

131
00:10:31,330 --> 00:10:33,900
So apparently Minato-senpai is taking care of her by himself.

132
00:10:58,870 --> 00:10:59,670
Um...

133
00:11:00,930 --> 00:11:02,770
Excuse me, Minato-senpai...

134
00:11:03,060 --> 00:11:03,970
Is he here?

135
00:11:04,500 --> 00:11:06,370
He's taking a break from school.

136
00:11:06,770 --> 00:11:08,630
His mom passed away.

137
00:11:22,730 --> 00:11:23,800
Minato.

138
00:11:26,570 --> 00:11:29,300
It's been so hard on you.

139
00:11:31,470 --> 00:11:35,630
Taking care of your mother all by yourself, day after day.

140
00:11:36,870 --> 00:11:38,130
And then she was just gone.

141
00:11:39,470 --> 00:11:40,570
Thank you so much.

142
00:11:59,870 --> 00:12:01,800
- Thank you.
- Thank you so much!

143
00:12:01,800 --> 00:12:03,200
I'm going now.

144
00:12:05,170 --> 00:12:06,630
Oh, Miu!

145
00:12:06,690 --> 00:12:09,000
Are you here to buy our sata-andagi again?
(Okinawa style sugar doughnuts)

146
00:12:09,020 --> 00:12:10,930
Because they're delicious!

147
00:12:11,330 --> 00:12:13,330
Ryusei, I'm glad to see your cast is off.

148
00:12:13,470 --> 00:12:14,330
Oh right.

149
00:12:14,400 --> 00:12:15,500
Back in top form!

150
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:18,170
Right, Miu.

151
00:12:18,250 --> 00:12:19,890
Did you meet up with Minato-senpai?

152
00:12:20,100 --> 00:12:21,600
Ah... no.

153
00:12:22,270 --> 00:12:24,310
It seems he hasn't been back to school.

154
00:12:24,340 --> 00:12:25,520
I see.

155
00:12:26,160 --> 00:12:27,080
I'm home.

156
00:12:27,470 --> 00:12:28,290
Welcome back.

157
00:13:18,600 --> 00:13:19,810
Um.

158
00:13:23,000 --> 00:13:23,900
Excuse me!

159
00:13:33,390 --> 00:13:37,660
I'm Tamashiro Miu in first year class one.

160
00:13:38,570 --> 00:13:40,520
Minato-senpai, yes?

161
00:13:41,430 --> 00:13:42,300
What is it?

162
00:13:51,570 --> 00:13:53,470
You dropped this MD,

163
00:13:53,480 --> 00:13:55,730
when we bumped into each other at the hospital.

164
00:14:12,010 --> 00:14:12,600
This...

165
00:14:13,400 --> 00:14:15,330
That one is mine.

166
00:14:19,600 --> 00:14:20,400
Sorry.

167
00:14:22,700 --> 00:14:23,840
It's the same album.

168
00:14:30,800 --> 00:14:32,730
Aren't you coming back to school?

169
00:14:54,330 --> 00:14:54,970
Here.

170
00:14:55,220 --> 00:14:57,710
This is the world's most delicious sata-andagi.

171
00:15:00,730 --> 00:15:03,800
It's from a shop run by the family of a childhood friend.

172
00:15:03,850 --> 00:15:05,480
The brown sugar ones are the best.

173
00:15:28,070 --> 00:15:28,870
It's good.

174
00:15:38,730 --> 00:15:39,530
I'll see you.

175
00:15:45,470 --> 00:15:46,530
Minato-senpai.

176
00:15:49,670 --> 00:15:50,790
See you at school.

177
00:15:55,150 --> 00:15:55,970
Thanks.

178
00:16:26,170 --> 00:16:26,930
Miu.

179
00:16:27,310 --> 00:16:28,570
Go take your bath.

180
00:16:28,700 --> 00:16:31,380
Don't just barge into my room like that, Mom!

181
00:16:31,870 --> 00:16:32,770
Fine.

182
00:16:57,500 --> 00:16:59,930
Makiya Minato.

183
00:17:07,330 --> 00:17:09,200
Long time no see.

184
00:17:21,810 --> 00:17:25,190
Songs to cheer you up - Part 1!!

185
00:17:48,760 --> 00:17:51,220
Recommendations (1)

186
00:18:19,120 --> 00:18:21,210
Songs to cheer you up - Part 2!!

187
00:18:53,000 --> 00:18:54,000
Smells good.

188
00:18:55,770 --> 00:18:56,830
I really like...

189
00:19:00,730 --> 00:19:01,530
This scent.

190
00:19:47,690 --> 00:19:51,800
The sea really seems to go on forever.

191
00:19:52,970 --> 00:19:56,680
I wonder what the world is like beyond.

192
00:19:57,330 --> 00:19:58,820
I want to go see.

193
00:19:59,370 --> 00:20:00,810
What lies beyond.

194
00:20:03,870 --> 00:20:07,030
What are you doing after graduation, Minato-senpai?

195
00:20:09,070 --> 00:20:11,130
I'm planning to go to university in Tokyo.

196
00:20:14,470 --> 00:20:16,700
I was torn if I should stay in Okinawa.

197
00:20:18,300 --> 00:20:20,350
I want to challenge myself to do what I want to do.

198
00:20:21,170 --> 00:20:22,870
I want to live without regrets.

199
00:20:29,130 --> 00:20:31,000
If it's Minato-senpai,

200
00:20:31,320 --> 00:20:32,900
you can be anything you want,

201
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:34,840
anywhere you go.

202
00:20:42,470 --> 00:20:45,170
What is it that you want to do, Minato-senpai?

203
00:20:47,370 --> 00:20:51,270
Music saved me when I was going through difficult times.

204
00:20:52,470 --> 00:20:53,670
That's why someday,

205
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:55,800
I'd like to make my own music.

206
00:20:58,070 --> 00:20:59,770
Not just someone who enjoys music,

207
00:20:59,770 --> 00:21:01,270
but who creates it too.

208
00:21:02,500 --> 00:21:03,700
That's awesome.

209
00:21:08,530 --> 00:21:09,800
And you, Tamashiro-san?

210
00:21:10,730 --> 00:21:12,400
What are your dreams?

211
00:21:13,570 --> 00:21:17,300
My mother works as an interpreter.

212
00:21:17,570 --> 00:21:19,170
I've always looked up to her.

213
00:21:19,950 --> 00:21:23,080
That's why I'm doing my best studying English.

214
00:21:23,270 --> 00:21:24,200
I see.

215
00:21:26,470 --> 00:21:29,300
But the future for me,

216
00:21:29,570 --> 00:21:32,370
Still seems so far away.

217
00:21:33,980 --> 00:21:36,150
I'm having fun now,

218
00:21:36,150 --> 00:21:38,770
I wish it could go on forever.

219
00:21:40,770 --> 00:21:43,400
I know that's impossible of course.

220
00:21:47,400 --> 00:21:48,200
But...

221
00:21:49,270 --> 00:21:51,800
I believe there are things that never change.

222
00:22:10,570 --> 00:22:12,220
Say cheese!

223
00:22:20,930 --> 00:22:22,380
Minato-senpai!

224
00:22:22,480 --> 00:22:24,760
Congratulations on your graduation!

225
00:22:26,010 --> 00:22:28,870
Please take this, congratulations!

226
00:22:28,870 --> 00:22:31,430
Minato-senpai, can we take a picture with you?

227
00:22:51,890 --> 00:22:54,000
What are you doing sitting there?

228
00:22:54,130 --> 00:22:55,090
Going home?

229
00:22:56,230 --> 00:22:57,010
Yeah.

230
00:22:59,170 --> 00:23:02,240
It's your leap year birthday today.

231
00:23:03,170 --> 00:23:07,020
I bet your mom is going all out and preparing a feast.

232
00:23:09,170 --> 00:23:12,800
I don't want to celebrate my birthday this year.

233
00:23:19,460 --> 00:23:20,390
Miu.

234
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:23,920
What?

235
00:23:24,370 --> 00:23:25,000
Ah.

236
00:23:25,620 --> 00:23:26,650
Ah... em...

237
00:23:32,060 --> 00:23:33,500
What the...

238
00:23:35,430 --> 00:23:36,690
Funny face!

239
00:23:36,690 --> 00:23:38,030
Stop it!

240
00:23:48,540 --> 00:23:50,010
You're sure you don't want to go?

241
00:23:50,880 --> 00:23:52,430
To look for Minato-senpai.

242
00:24:08,870 --> 00:24:10,330
Minato-senpai.

243
00:24:19,980 --> 00:24:22,200
It's Leap Day today.

244
00:24:22,600 --> 00:24:25,300
It's my birthday today.

245
00:24:26,100 --> 00:24:27,070
I know.

246
00:24:27,190 --> 00:24:27,930
Eh?

247
00:24:28,390 --> 00:24:29,990
How do you know?

248
00:24:30,300 --> 00:24:31,130
Well.

249
00:24:33,500 --> 00:24:34,100
Okay.

250
00:24:34,170 --> 00:24:36,440
Minato-senpai, do you know this then?

251
00:24:37,110 --> 00:24:39,530
On the 29th of February,

252
00:24:39,530 --> 00:24:41,670
if a woman proposes to a man,

253
00:24:41,700 --> 00:24:43,260
he can't refuse.

254
00:24:43,260 --> 00:24:44,490
What's that?

255
00:24:44,770 --> 00:24:49,420
I think it's some ancient law in Ireland, or some other country.

256
00:24:49,420 --> 00:24:50,860
That's a weird law.

257
00:24:51,150 --> 00:24:52,390
We're in Japan.

258
00:24:53,020 --> 00:24:54,270
I know.

259
00:24:54,430 --> 00:24:55,970
I'm just saying.

260
00:24:59,100 --> 00:24:59,890
Okay then.

261
00:25:00,440 --> 00:25:02,300
Just for today,

262
00:25:02,910 --> 00:25:05,250
I'll grant you anything that you wish for.

263
00:25:06,800 --> 00:25:07,870
Because it's your birthday.

264
00:25:08,370 --> 00:25:09,170
It's special.

265
00:25:11,300 --> 00:25:13,470
You'll really grant me any wish?

266
00:25:14,070 --> 00:25:14,870
Anything?

267
00:25:15,380 --> 00:25:16,910
As long as it's within my means.

268
00:25:25,270 --> 00:25:26,250
I like you.

269
00:25:26,570 --> 00:25:27,960
Please go out with me.

270
00:25:34,730 --> 00:25:35,530
I lied.

271
00:25:36,130 --> 00:25:38,480
Please forget everything I just said.

272
00:25:38,970 --> 00:25:39,770
Eh?

273
00:25:40,690 --> 00:25:43,070
You can just say no to that.

274
00:25:47,100 --> 00:25:50,380
I wonder what I should wish for...

275
00:25:51,930 --> 00:25:56,170
Ah, someday I'd like to listen to a song written by Minato-senpai.

276
00:25:59,710 --> 00:26:01,040
I don't want to say no.

277
00:26:03,050 --> 00:26:03,810
Huh?

278
00:26:14,600 --> 00:26:15,400
I like you.

279
00:26:16,870 --> 00:26:18,150
Won't you go out with me?

280
00:26:25,500 --> 00:26:26,300
Yes!

281
00:26:51,130 --> 00:26:51,930
Alright.

282
00:26:52,370 --> 00:26:53,470
I'll be in touch.

283
00:26:54,700 --> 00:26:55,370
Okay.

284
00:27:06,130 --> 00:27:07,200
Minato-senpai.

285
00:27:08,370 --> 00:27:12,500
I'm going to Tokyo after I graduate high school.

286
00:27:13,730 --> 00:27:17,850
I also want to see what lies beyond the sea.

