You were looking at interpreter jobs in Okinawa the other day.

567
00:48:24,650 --> 00:48:25,300
Yeah.

568
00:48:26,950 --> 00:48:29,250
But it's okay.

569
00:48:29,810 --> 00:48:30,800
I've made up my mind.

570
00:48:33,260 --> 00:48:34,630
What do you mean?

571
00:48:37,100 --> 00:48:39,660
It's been your dream since you were a kid.

572
00:48:41,040 --> 00:48:42,900
Does it matter so little to you?

573
00:48:44,570 --> 00:48:46,300
I was serious about it.

574
00:48:47,130 --> 00:48:49,170
But aside from our dreams,

575
00:48:49,400 --> 00:48:52,600
Everyday life is also important too.

576
00:48:55,870 --> 00:48:59,470
I think being able to continue the life I have now,

577
00:48:59,470 --> 00:49:00,800
is also a kind of dream.

578
00:49:04,540 --> 00:49:06,370
So you like the way things are now.

579
00:49:07,170 --> 00:49:09,470
How long are you going to keep saying that?

580
00:49:10,930 --> 00:49:13,770
You need to give serious thought to your own future.

581
00:49:14,800 --> 00:49:15,870
I am thinking about it.

582
00:49:16,700 --> 00:49:18,770
Even if I seem unsure about things.

583
00:49:20,760 --> 00:49:24,500
But it's because I want to be with you forever, Minato.

584
00:49:25,900 --> 00:49:26,700
Because?

585
00:49:32,600 --> 00:49:34,250
There's no such thing as forever.

586
00:49:49,090 --> 00:49:50,470
I need to take a walk.

587
00:49:51,700 --> 00:49:52,800
You should go to bed first.

588
00:50:49,370 --> 00:50:50,240
Miu.

589
00:50:53,870 --> 00:50:55,480
I'll be done with work early today.

590
00:50:55,770 --> 00:50:57,500
Why don't we go out for dinner tonight?

591
00:51:18,850 --> 00:51:20,490
The place I applied to today.

592
00:51:20,670 --> 00:51:22,870
Is pretty close to your office.

593
00:51:23,620 --> 00:51:25,730
If I get the job.

594
00:51:25,740 --> 00:51:28,360
We could take the leap and move closer to work.

595
00:51:28,840 --> 00:51:30,770
It'll make commuting a lot easier.

596
00:51:31,070 --> 00:51:32,220
Yeah, that's true.

597
00:51:33,530 --> 00:51:36,700
Well, I've got to get the job first, don't I?

598
00:51:42,800 --> 00:51:43,600
Miu.

599
00:51:44,300 --> 00:51:45,840
Hmm? What is it?

600
00:51:47,930 --> 00:51:48,870
Oh nothing.

601
00:51:49,290 --> 00:51:51,060
What is it...

602
00:51:51,120 --> 00:51:53,210
I was thinking how you always look like you enjoy your food.

603
00:51:53,720 --> 00:51:55,090
It's because it is delicious.

604
00:51:55,090 --> 00:51:56,080
Heh, yeah.

605
00:51:57,930 --> 00:51:59,540
If I'm with you, Minato.

606
00:51:59,900 --> 00:52:01,030
Everything tastes good.

607
00:52:05,450 --> 00:52:07,590
Ah, that was delicious.

608
00:52:08,090 --> 00:52:10,270
It's been a while since we had dinner together.

609
00:52:16,940 --> 00:52:18,000
I'm sorry about everything.

610
00:52:20,370 --> 00:52:22,270
All I do is work everyday.

611
00:52:22,600 --> 00:52:24,000
Come home late.

612
00:52:24,870 --> 00:52:28,000
I haven't been there for you at all for your job search.

613
00:52:29,400 --> 00:52:30,800
You're busy with work.

614
00:52:31,130 --> 00:52:32,100
Can't be helped.

615
00:52:33,870 --> 00:52:36,770
I'm sorry about the other day.

616
00:52:38,530 --> 00:52:41,130
You take care of everything around the apartment.

617
00:52:41,730 --> 00:52:43,470
I said we should go on a trip.

618
00:52:44,500 --> 00:52:45,900
But we never did.

619
00:52:48,100 --> 00:52:50,540
When work calms down for you,

620
00:52:50,540 --> 00:52:52,870
let's take a week off and go somewhere.

621
00:52:53,270 --> 00:52:55,400
Maybe go abroad even, what about it?

622
00:52:56,720 --> 00:52:57,560
I'm sorry.

623
00:52:58,950 --> 00:53:00,830
I already said it's fine.

624
00:53:08,270 --> 00:53:09,070
Minato.

625
00:53:10,080 --> 00:53:10,900
What's wrong?

626
00:53:15,400 --> 00:53:16,200
Miu.

627
00:53:18,010 --> 00:53:18,700
I...

628
00:53:23,570 --> 00:53:24,370
I...

629
00:53:26,140 --> 00:53:28,000
can't be with you anymore, Miu.

630
00:53:30,500 --> 00:53:31,300
Eh?

631
00:53:33,770 --> 00:53:34,730
Let's break up.

632
00:53:37,970 --> 00:53:38,870
Why?

633
00:53:40,400 --> 00:53:41,200
Sorry.

634
00:53:44,100 --> 00:53:46,200
You can't just say sorry, I don't get it.

635
00:53:49,070 --> 00:53:51,500
There's nothing more I can do for you, Miu.

636
00:53:51,870 --> 00:53:52,870
That's not true.

637
00:53:52,870 --> 00:53:53,750
Miu.

638
00:53:55,500 --> 00:53:56,300
No, no.

639
00:53:58,370 --> 00:53:59,330
No, no...

640
00:53:59,930 --> 00:54:01,200
Why, Minato?

641
00:54:04,330 --> 00:54:05,530
Please break up with me.

642
00:54:08,830 --> 00:54:09,970
I beg you.

643
00:55:57,800 --> 00:56:01,380
I love you.

644
00:56:46,980 --> 00:56:47,870
Miu.

645
00:56:57,440 --> 00:56:59,130
Sorry to keep calling.

646
00:57:05,650 --> 00:57:08,700
You left this behind in the apartment.

647
00:57:11,320 --> 00:57:13,400
I said you could throw it away.

648
00:57:18,470 --> 00:57:20,100
There's something I want to tell you...

649
00:57:22,250 --> 00:57:23,100
What is it?

650
00:57:27,170 --> 00:57:28,280
I...

651
00:57:50,640 --> 00:57:51,430
Here.

652
00:57:59,870 --> 00:58:01,100
I can't accept this.

653
00:58:03,860 --> 00:58:07,670
I don't love you anymore, Miu.

654
00:58:10,950 --> 00:58:12,500
And I don't plan to see you again.

655
00:58:16,920 --> 00:58:18,430
Please forget me.

656
00:58:51,550 --> 00:58:56,140
Tokyo

657
00:59:23,200 --> 00:59:25,360
I wanna go home.

658
00:59:35,270 --> 00:59:36,810
Mommy...

659
00:59:41,470 --> 00:59:42,270
Kotaro?

660
00:59:44,130 --> 00:59:46,200
Eh? Eh? What are you doing here?

661
00:59:50,330 --> 00:59:51,570
Kotaro!!

662
00:59:51,880 --> 00:59:53,010
What!

663
00:59:56,820 --> 00:59:57,910
Thanks.

664
00:59:59,950 --> 01:00:01,290
Scary.

665
01:00:13,060 --> 01:00:14,620
I was worried about you.

666
01:00:15,000 --> 01:00:16,300
So I followed you.

667
01:00:17,760 --> 01:00:20,450
Wait, so you were nearby the whole time?

668
01:00:21,070 --> 01:00:23,630
I thought I could help if anything happened.

669
01:00:23,630 --> 01:00:24,730
So I was keeping a watch out.

670
01:00:25,570 --> 01:00:26,610
What the heck?

671
01:00:27,670 --> 01:00:29,690
You should've said something right from the start.

672
01:00:31,870 --> 01:00:37,330
Boy, I really can't figure out the streets of Tokyo.

673
01:00:38,370 --> 01:00:39,370
I'm done.

674
01:00:40,470 --> 01:00:42,300
I want to go back to Okinawa.

675
01:00:46,270 --> 01:00:51,500
But your dad asked you do something really important for him, didn't he?

676
01:00:53,000 --> 01:00:54,470
How do you know?

677
01:01:00,530 --> 01:01:01,370
Speaking of.

678
01:01:04,800 --> 01:01:06,070
Let's see what this is.

679
01:01:18,940 --> 01:01:19,830
What's wrong?

680
01:02:22,970 --> 01:02:27,980
Okinawa

681
01:02:51,430 --> 01:02:53,620
Miu!

682
01:02:54,570 --> 01:02:55,800
Ryusei.

683
01:03:01,530 --> 01:03:02,680
Welcome home.

684
01:03:02,910 --> 01:03:05,500
I heard from your mom that you're coming back today.

685
01:03:06,570 --> 01:03:07,540
I'm back.

686
01:03:08,630 --> 01:03:10,270
Come, I'll carry that.

687
01:03:15,600 --> 01:03:16,300
You're...

688
01:03:21,300 --> 01:03:24,530
Why didn't you say anything to Minato-senpai?

689
01:03:29,330 --> 01:03:32,000
You may have broken up but you should still talk this through.

690
01:03:33,930 --> 01:03:36,670
Minato doesn't have any feelings for me anymore,

691
01:03:37,200 --> 01:03:38,330
it would just hurt even more.

692
01:03:39,800 --> 01:03:41,700
This is not the time to say things like that.

693
01:03:42,300 --> 01:03:44,100
What are your plans?

694
01:03:47,730 --> 01:03:51,600
My job search hasn't been going well.

695
01:03:53,000 --> 01:03:56,930
I thought of giving up my dreams of being an interpreter.

696
01:03:58,730 --> 01:04:00,600
I thought as long as I could be with Minato,

697
01:04:00,970 --> 01:04:02,570
everything would be fine.

698
01:04:06,070 --> 01:04:10,670
That's probably why Minato got frustrated and left.

699
01:04:13,930 --> 01:04:18,000
But then I found out I was pregnant.

700
01:04:19,500 --> 01:04:22,070
I was overwhelmed and my mind was a blank.

701
01:04:28,770 --> 01:04:33,090
But I realised I want to keep the baby.

702
01:04:36,600 --> 01:04:40,200
And I don't want to give up my dream of being an interpreter.

703
01:04:41,470 --> 01:04:44,970
Just as I looked up to my mom when I was a kid.

704
01:04:46,270 --> 01:04:50,330
I want my child to look at me the same way.

705
01:05:02,730 --> 01:05:03,900
I'm sorry.

706
01:05:05,930 --> 01:05:08,530
But I want to have this baby.

707
01:05:10,760 --> 01:05:12,160
You want this baby?

708
01:05:12,870 --> 01:05:15,320
What about university?

709
01:05:15,730 --> 01:05:17,600
I'll be sure to finish university.

710
01:05:18,530 --> 01:05:21,370
And I'll look for a job.

711
01:05:22,370 --> 01:05:23,700
Please.

712
01:05:25,170 --> 01:05:26,740
Who is he?

713
01:05:35,230 --> 01:05:36,070
Sorry!

714
01:05:37,440 --> 01:05:38,500
It's me.

715
01:05:39,530 --> 01:05:40,330
Ryusei...

716
01:05:40,530 --> 01:05:42,300
- What...
- It's me.

717
01:05:43,310 --> 01:05:44,440
I'm the father.

718
01:05:48,640 --> 01:05:50,600
I'll take full responsibility and raise the child.

719
01:05:51,500 --> 01:05:52,300
So...

720
01:05:53,300 --> 01:05:54,470
I beg you.

721
01:05:59,500 --> 01:06:01,970
Hey wai-... where are you going...

722
01:06:07,770 --> 01:06:10,050
What did you mean doing that?

723
01:06:10,570 --> 01:06:12,470
Sorry. Are you shocked?

724
01:06:13,130 --> 01:06:15,070
Don't joke about things like that.

725
01:06:17,370 --> 01:06:18,300
I wasn't joking.

726
01:06:19,070 --> 01:06:20,130
I'm serious.

727
01:06:26,000 --> 01:06:28,470
I've tried giving up so many times but...

728
01:06:29,330 --> 01:06:30,330
I just couldn't.

729
01:06:32,500 --> 01:06:33,300
I...

730
01:06:34,400 --> 01:06:36,730
I've always loved you, Miu.

731
01:06:37,900 --> 01:06:38,700
What?

732
01:06:41,000 --> 01:06:43,130
As I thought, you never realised it.

733
01:06:44,100 --> 01:06:45,870
You really are dense.

734
01:06:48,530 --> 01:06:49,330
Sorry.

735
01:06:51,300 --> 01:06:53,370
I hadn't planned on ever telling you this.

736
01:06:55,330 --> 01:06:59,100
But when you said you wanted to keep fighting.

737
01:06:59,800 --> 01:07:03,070
I knew I wanted to be by your side supporting you.

738
01:07:04,700 --> 01:07:08,400
I want us to raise this child together..

739
01:07:13,770 --> 01:07:14,930
I'm sorry, Ryusei.

740
01:07:16,500 --> 01:07:20,400
I don't plan on getting married.

741
01:07:23,020 --> 01:07:27,030
Are you still in love with Minato-senpai?

742
01:07:35,870 --> 01:07:36,990
That's okay, you know.

743
01:07:38,070 --> 01:07:39,370
Let me be by your side.

744
01:07:41,970 --> 01:07:43,900
Who knows what the future holds?

745
01:07:44,570 --> 01:07:48,130
You might end up completely smitten with me.

746
01:07:50,770 --> 01:07:52,060
Smitten?

747
01:07:58,400 --> 01:08:00,670
I want you to keep smiling like that, Miu.

748
01:08:05,800 --> 01:08:07,400
I'll see you.

749
01:08:37,600 --> 01:08:41,870
Minato, I brought something for you.

750
01:08:45,800 --> 01:08:46,600
Here.

751
01:08:47,670 --> 01:08:48,670
It's from everyone.

752
01:08:49,130 --> 01:08:49,930
Thank you.

753
01:08:50,870 --> 01:08:52,900
Doesn't it look just like you?

754
01:09:05,500 --> 01:09:07,770
I heard this from our junior in the club.

755
01:09:08,500 --> 01:09:11,930
Miu-chan is going back to Okinawa after graduation.

756
01:09:14,700 --> 01:09:15,730
I see.

757
01:09:19,330 --> 01:09:22,070
Call me whenever you need anything.

758
01:09:22,270 --> 01:09:25,770
I don't want you to feel lonely, so I'm happy to come hang out.

759
01:09:27,770 --> 01:09:29,400
You must be busy though, Kasumi.

760
01:09:30,330 --> 01:09:31,870
Don't worry about me.

761
01:09:32,470 --> 01:09:33,900
Focus on your work.

762
01:09:35,170 --> 01:09:37,570
I'm looking forward to your debut.

763
01:09:41,670 --> 01:09:42,780
Don't say that.

764
01:09:43,930 --> 01:09:45,700
Focus on getting well soon,

765
01:09:46,050 --> 01:09:47,810
So we can fulfill our dreams together.

766
01:09:48,060 --> 01:09:52,070
I'll be waiting for you to come back, however long it takes.

767
01:10:03,000 --> 01:10:05,530
Just say the word, and I will.

768
01:10:35,670 --> 01:10:37,170
What are you listening to?

769
01:10:45,900 --> 01:10:46,700
Here.

770
01:10:46,930 --> 01:10:47,800
Thank you.

771
01:11:06,670 --> 01:11:08,100
I haven't seen that in a while.

772
01:11:09,500 --> 01:11:11,570
A smile on Minato's face..

773
01:11:21,300 --> 01:11:22,300
I'm sorry.

774
01:11:23,600 --> 01:11:25,530
Leaving you all alone.

775
01:11:27,470 --> 01:11:29,870
Causing you nothing but pain.

776
01:11:32,270 --> 01:11:33,570
What are you saying?

777
01:11:36,400 --> 01:11:41,900
I want you to always be smiling, Minato.

778
01:11:45,570 --> 01:11:47,000
Please don't say such things.

779
01:11:52,000 --> 01:11:54,010
I can't wait to hear

780
01:11:55,870 --> 01:11:57,920
a song written by Minato.

781
01:12:38,000 --> 01:12:39,570
After Mom died.

782
01:12:40,370 --> 01:12:41,600
Nothing...

783
01:12:42,530 --> 01:12:44,130
Nothing mattered anymore.

784
01:12:46,900 --> 01:12:47,970
Whether it's school,

785
01:12:48,170 --> 01:12:49,400
or the future,

786
01:12:50,570 --> 01:12:52,700
I didn't want to think about anything.

787
01:12:54,100 --> 01:12:56,470
Nothing brought me joy.

788
01:12:57,130 --> 01:12:59,450
Nothing I ate tasted of anything.

789
01:13:01,070 --> 01:13:01,870
Here.

790
01:13:01,970 --> 01:13:05,070
This is the world's most delicious sata-andagi.

791
01:13:09,330 --> 01:13:10,850
For the first time in a while,

792
01:13:11,330 --> 01:13:12,470
I could taste something.

793
01:13:15,670 --> 01:13:17,730
How you made everything you ate look delicious.

794
01:13:20,400 --> 01:13:22,970
How you looked so happy listening to music.

795
01:13:23,820 --> 01:13:24,840
I loved it all.

796
01:13:25,700 --> 01:13:27,470
If it's Minato-senpai,

797
01:13:27,670 --> 01:13:29,400
you can be anything you want,

798
01:13:29,770 --> 01:13:31,530
anywhere you go.

799
01:13:31,870 --> 01:13:34,170
Your words gave me the push I needed.

800
01:13:34,500 --> 01:13:37,360
Someday I'd like to listen to a song written by Minato-senpai.

801
01:13:38,660 --> 01:13:42,270
I could dream once again.

802
01:13:45,530 --> 01:13:51,930
"May these happy days last forever."

803
01:13:53,270 --> 01:13:55,000
That was what I wished for.

804
01:13:56,970 --> 01:13:57,770
But then...

805
01:14:03,510 --> 01:14:07,220
Observation

806
01:14:04,100 --> 01:14:06,930
You have acute myeloid leukaemia.

807
01:14:07,330 --> 01:14:09,260
I'll make the arrangements for hospitalisation.

808
01:14:09,260 --> 01:14:10,930
You need to be admitted today.

809
01:14:11,130 --> 01:14:13,070
Please inform your family as well.

810
01:14:13,200 --> 01:14:14,530
W-wait a minute.

811
01:14:17,200 --> 01:14:18,900
It's too sudden... all this.

812
01:14:25,130 --> 01:14:26,670
Why me?

813
01:14:27,800 --> 01:14:30,100
When I've finally found happiness.

814
01:14:35,130 --> 01:14:36,530
If I'd told Miu.

815
01:14:37,170 --> 01:14:37,970
Surely.

816
01:14:38,870 --> 01:14:40,870
She would have sacrificed everything.

817
01:14:41,870 --> 01:14:43,300
To stay by my side.

818
01:14:44,100 --> 01:14:45,570
There's no such thing as forever.

819
01:14:48,130 --> 01:14:49,800
If we had stayed together.

820
01:14:50,730 --> 01:14:52,670
I would only be holding her back.

821
01:14:56,570 --> 01:14:57,970
I didn't want that.

822
01:15:07,770 --> 01:15:08,570
But..

823
01:15:10,530 --> 01:15:11,900
I didn't want to let you go.

824
01:15:13,700 --> 01:15:14,700
More than anything...

825
01:15:16,370 --> 01:15:18,400
I wanted Miu by my side.

826
01:15:20,470 --> 01:15:21,270
Miu.

827
01:15:21,370 --> 01:15:22,400
Hmm? What is it?

828
01:15:25,300 --> 01:15:27,000
Oh nothing.

829
01:15:27,400 --> 01:15:28,700
What is it?

830
01:15:29,170 --> 01:15:30,850
How I wanted to tell you

831
01:15:31,390 --> 01:15:32,490
... about my illness.

832
01:15:33,630 --> 01:15:34,410
But...

833
01:15:35,800 --> 01:15:37,970
I just want to see you keep smiling.

834
01:15:38,900 --> 01:15:40,570
And I couldn't bring myself to say anything.

835
01:15:41,770 --> 01:15:42,870
Please break up with me.

836
01:15:47,270 --> 01:15:48,070
In the end,

837
01:15:49,500 --> 01:15:51,600
I was afraid of dragging Miu into it.

838
01:15:54,700 --> 01:15:55,500
So I ran away.

839
01:16:28,570 --> 01:16:33,990
Acute Myeloid Leukaemia
Chemotherapy Treatment - Patient Consent Form

840
01:17:25,470 --> 01:17:26,270
Yo.

841
01:17:26,730 --> 01:17:28,170
Weather's nice today, huh?

842
01:17:29,100 --> 01:17:30,300
Ryota-san.

843
01:17:30,800 --> 01:17:31,690
Don't you have to work?

844
01:17:31,830 --> 01:17:32,700
Skipped out.

845
01:17:32,700 --> 01:17:34,100
Don't tell the boss, eh.

846
01:17:36,330 --> 01:17:38,070
I'm really sorry,

847
01:17:38,470 --> 01:17:39,670
for being such a burden.

848
01:17:40,200 --> 01:17:42,270
Nobody thinks you're a burden.

849
01:17:42,770 --> 01:17:44,670
Don't worry about anything to do with work.

850
01:17:44,670 --> 01:17:45,970
Focus on getting well,

851
01:17:46,120 --> 01:17:47,430
so you can come back soon.

852
01:17:50,060 --> 01:17:50,800
Speaking of...

853
01:17:52,970 --> 01:17:53,770
Here.

854
01:17:54,200 --> 01:17:56,200
It got mixed up with a bunch of files at work.

855
01:17:57,370 --> 01:17:58,970
It's something important to you, isn't it?

856
01:17:59,330 --> 01:18:00,330
What was it again?

857
01:18:00,870 --> 01:18:02,960
A leap year promise?

858
01:18:04,770 --> 01:18:06,130
It's okay.

859
01:18:08,130 --> 01:18:09,400
It's all in the past.

860
01:18:13,700 --> 01:18:16,000
Aren't you going to regret it?

861
01:18:18,070 --> 01:18:20,570
Why did you break up with her?

862
01:18:21,470 --> 01:18:23,130
She's someone very special, isn't she?

863
01:18:27,070 --> 01:18:28,000
She's special...

864
01:18:29,330 --> 01:18:31,000
And it's because she's so precious to me...

865
01:18:32,800 --> 01:18:34,870
That I want her to be happy.

866
01:18:37,130 --> 01:18:39,070
You're strong, Minato.

867
01:18:40,970 --> 01:18:42,330
I'm not strong at all.

868
01:18:43,930 --> 01:18:46,330
I wasn't mentally prepared for this at all.

869
01:18:47,870 --> 01:18:50,530
Every time I think I was going to die...

870
01:18:51,770 --> 01:18:54,070
I would see Miu's face.

871
01:18:57,500 --> 01:18:58,370
Minato,

872
01:18:58,730 --> 01:19:01,200
you said this when you joined us.

873
01:19:02,330 --> 01:19:05,530
Music saved you.

874
01:19:06,100 --> 01:19:07,200
That some day,

875
01:19:07,800 --> 01:19:10,470
you wanted to make music like that too.

876
01:19:16,160 --> 01:19:19,470
There's someone waiting for you to write them a song, isn't there?

877
01:19:29,770 --> 01:19:30,870
I'm sorry.

878
01:19:43,890 --> 01:19:47,980
Okinawa

879
01:19:45,100 --> 01:19:47,930
We can narrow down the location after the site inspections tomorrow.

880
01:20:02,600 --> 01:20:04,070
Each place is so beautiful.

881
01:20:04,070 --> 01:20:05,700
It's really hard to choose.

882
01:20:05,700 --> 01:20:08,030
But they'd like to pick the perfect location.

883
01:20:32,030 --> 01:20:32,600
Yo.

884
01:20:33,170 --> 01:20:33,970
Ryusei.

885
01:20:40,570 --> 01:20:42,000
How's work?

886
01:20:42,500 --> 01:20:43,300
Going well?

887
01:20:44,170 --> 01:20:44,970
Mmmm...

888
01:20:45,650 --> 01:20:47,320
I still have some way to go.

889
01:20:47,670 --> 01:20:49,480
Gotta work hard at it.

890
01:20:50,770 --> 01:20:54,070
You know, your parents are both worried about you.

891
01:20:54,870 --> 01:20:57,670
Juggling both work and caring for Himari,

892
01:20:57,770 --> 01:20:59,500
giving your all to everything.

893
01:20:59,800 --> 01:21:01,730
Careful that you don't collapse one of these days.

894
01:21:03,170 --> 01:21:04,300
I'll be fine.

895
01:21:04,600 --> 01:21:05,900
You're such a worrywart.

896
01:21:12,730 --> 01:21:15,730
You haven't been in contact with Minato-senpai?

897
01:21:18,300 --> 01:21:18,950
Yeah.

898
01:21:20,700 --> 01:21:23,570
We've never been in touch.

899
01:21:26,270 --> 01:21:30,470
I don't know where he is, what he's doing, but...

900
01:21:32,130 --> 01:21:33,670
I hope he's doing well.

901
01:21:39,470 --> 01:21:44,730
Minato took me somewhere far beyond these waters.

902
01:21:47,570 --> 01:21:49,170
I couldn't have done it by myself.

903
01:21:51,570 --> 01:21:52,570
I see.

904
01:21:54,070 --> 01:21:55,070
Did you have fun?

905
01:21:57,980 --> 01:21:58,600
Yeah.

906
01:22:01,700 --> 01:22:03,800
I had so much fun.

907
01:22:26,070 --> 01:22:28,170
This helmet is just for you.

908
01:22:28,600 --> 01:22:30,400
I don't want to hear that it's lame.

909
01:23:09,530 --> 01:23:12,270
You're going to dry yourself out crying like that.

910
01:23:13,500 --> 01:23:14,400
I'm not crying.

911
01:23:17,670 --> 01:23:18,470
Miu.

912
01:23:18,870 --> 01:23:19,930
Look there.

913
01:23:21,600 --> 01:23:23,330
There's still so much to see out there.

914
01:23:24,530 --> 01:23:25,770
For you, for me.

915
01:23:26,200 --> 01:23:27,200
Himari too.

916
01:23:28,800 --> 01:23:32,870
We've got a long life ahead of us, we'll keep going forever.

917
01:24:15,000 --> 01:24:17,040
Makiya-san, are you ready?

918
01:24:17,210 --> 01:24:19,200
Yes, coming.

919
01:24:23,200 --> 01:24:25,160
One, two... Minato!

920
01:24:25,170 --> 01:24:27,220
Congrats on getting discharged!

921
01:24:28,070 --> 01:24:29,130
What a surprise!

922
01:24:29,360 --> 01:24:31,270
- But why?
- It's a happy occasion.

923
01:24:31,370 --> 01:24:32,200
So we're here.

924
01:24:36,000 --> 01:24:38,200
I haven't laughed like that in such a long time.

925
01:24:39,100 --> 01:24:40,930
Ryota-san looked so happy.

926
01:24:41,370 --> 01:24:44,530
He's been waiting so long for you to come back to the office.

927
01:24:46,770 --> 01:24:49,010
And you're finally making your debut.

928
01:24:49,570 --> 01:24:50,770
That's really amazing.

929
01:24:51,800 --> 01:24:54,070
It's only just the beginning.

930
01:24:54,600 --> 01:24:57,370
I wonder what kind of world will unfold from here on.

931
01:24:57,470 --> 01:24:58,530
I'm excited.

932
01:25:00,750 --> 01:25:02,210
It's a new start for me too.

933
01:25:05,400 --> 01:25:08,170
I'm so glad you've recovered.

934
01:25:08,900 --> 01:25:11,400
You've fought hard these three years, Minato.

935
01:25:11,930 --> 01:25:12,730
Thank you.

936
01:25:13,770 --> 01:25:15,770
I'm really grateful to you, Kasumi.

937
01:25:21,290 --> 01:25:24,230
Enough time has passed so I can say this.

938
01:25:24,930 --> 01:25:25,730
You know...

939
01:25:26,370 --> 01:25:30,400
I really liked you back in university.

940
01:25:31,730 --> 01:25:32,530
Eh?

941
01:25:33,170 --> 01:25:34,730
Ahhh, got that off my chest.

942
01:25:34,800 --> 01:25:37,000
Just so you know, I'm speaking in past tense.

943
01:25:39,730 --> 01:25:41,130
I had no idea.

944
01:25:41,900 --> 01:25:44,900
Minato, you're dense as a brick.

945
01:25:45,000 --> 01:25:49,870
Besides, you were completely devoted to Miu from the moment you met.

946
01:25:50,370 --> 01:25:51,800
I never stood a chance.

947
01:25:54,100 --> 01:25:59,500
But that's what I liked most about you.

948
01:26:01,700 --> 01:26:04,200
And that's the end of the story.

949
01:26:04,670 --> 01:26:07,170
I hope we can stay best friends from here on.

950
01:26:10,330 --> 01:26:11,130
Kasumi.

951
01:26:15,970 --> 01:26:16,770
Thank you.

952
01:26:21,870 --> 01:26:24,970
Alright, that's enough.

953
01:26:28,270 --> 01:26:30,100
I heard about it from Ryota-san.

954
01:26:30,370 --> 01:26:32,300
About your promise to Miu-chan.

955
01:26:34,900 --> 01:26:35,800
It's tomorrow right?

956
01:26:35,930 --> 01:26:37,170
Going to Okinawa?

957
01:26:40,470 --> 01:26:43,670
I hope you fulfil your promise.

958
01:27:28,770 --> 01:27:30,730
Hey Himari, be careful when you're eating.

959
01:27:30,730 --> 01:27:31,900
Here we go.

960
01:27:34,670 --> 01:27:36,070
Is it yummy?

961
01:27:36,370 --> 01:27:37,170
Yes!

962
01:27:37,900 --> 01:27:40,200
Alright, let's have some banana too.

963
01:27:40,570 --> 01:27:42,330
Miu, I'll take over.

964
01:27:42,530 --> 01:27:43,330
Oh thanks!

965
01:27:43,930 --> 01:27:47,670
Now Himari, Papa's going to feed you now.

966
01:27:47,740 --> 01:27:48,570
Hima-chan,

967
01:27:48,970 --> 01:27:50,670
Let's eat with Papa!

968
01:27:50,770 --> 01:27:53,370
Alright, eat up!

969
01:27:53,730 --> 01:27:56,800
Ooh, you're eating kiwi.

970
01:28:00,930 --> 01:28:02,000
Ooh, yummy.

971
01:28:07,670 --> 01:28:10,500
Look at that face, looks just like Himari.

972
01:28:10,730 --> 01:28:11,530
You think?

973
01:28:14,500 --> 01:28:16,270
Tomorrow's the big day.

974
01:28:17,070 --> 01:28:17,930
Your wedding.

975
01:28:21,500 --> 01:28:22,770
When I think back,

976
01:28:23,300 --> 01:28:24,370
over these past three years.

977
01:28:25,170 --> 01:28:28,720
Ryusei has always been by my side, supporting me.

978
01:28:31,330 --> 01:28:35,530
That's why I proposed to Ryusei,

979
01:28:35,800 --> 01:28:38,130
Let's become a real family.

980
01:28:41,900 --> 01:28:44,300
Ryusei-kun once said to me,

981
01:28:45,070 --> 01:28:48,700
"Even if it takes ten years, twenty years."

982
01:28:48,730 --> 01:28:50,200
"I'll be waiting for Miu."

983
01:28:51,800 --> 01:28:54,740
"I don't mind waiting my whole life for her."

984
01:28:57,470 --> 01:28:59,930
You're a lucky girl.

985
01:29:07,130 --> 01:29:11,370
Do take care of Ryusei-kun and make him happy, okay?

986
01:29:14,440 --> 01:29:15,300
I will.

987
01:30:45,750 --> 01:30:47,220
Smells nice.

988
01:30:49,400 --> 01:30:50,570
Thank you very much!

989
01:30:54,330 --> 01:30:55,730
Ryusei-kun.

990
01:30:56,060 --> 01:30:57,100
Do you have a moment?

991
01:30:57,270 --> 01:30:58,280
Sure.

992
01:30:59,570 --> 01:31:05,600
Ryusei-kun, I've been meaning to thank you properly all this time.

993
01:31:07,770 --> 01:31:08,700
Ryusei-kun.

994
01:31:13,000 --> 01:31:15,260
My heartfelt thanks.

995
01:31:15,870 --> 01:31:17,170
Not just Miu,

996
01:31:17,270 --> 01:31:18,700
but also Himari.

997
01:31:19,330 --> 01:31:21,130
You accepted them unconditionally.

998
01:31:21,870 --> 01:31:23,130
What are you saying?

999
01:31:23,600 --> 01:31:26,000
I should be the one to thank you.

1000
01:31:27,700 --> 01:31:29,770
Becoming a father to Himari...

1001
01:31:30,730 --> 01:31:34,330
I'm the luckiest man in the world.

1002
01:31:36,170 --> 01:31:38,270
You're a good man, Ryusei-kun.

1003
01:31:40,000 --> 01:31:41,770
I know it's not going to be easy.

1004
01:31:43,730 --> 01:31:44,530
But for Miu,

1005
01:31:44,600 --> 01:31:45,930
and for Himari,

1006
01:31:47,570 --> 01:31:49,330
I entrust them to you.

1007
01:31:50,500 --> 01:31:52,700
Please stop, Father.

1008
01:31:52,930 --> 01:31:54,670
The real thing is tomorrow, after all.

1009
01:31:55,700 --> 01:31:56,530
That's true.

1010
01:31:57,200 --> 01:31:59,900
I look forward to tomorrow's wedding ceremony.

1011
01:32:00,400 --> 01:32:01,200
Yes.

1012
01:32:02,130 --> 01:32:02,930
See you.

1013
01:32:30,130 --> 01:32:30,930
Why?

1014
01:32:32,930 --> 01:32:34,570
Why now?

1015
01:32:38,200 --> 01:32:39,800
What's the point at this stage?

1016
01:32:40,170 --> 01:32:42,500
Are you trying to take Miu away from me again?

1017
01:32:43,270 --> 01:32:44,620
No, no I'm not.

1018
01:32:44,620 --> 01:32:46,330
Well then, why are you here?

1019
01:32:47,900 --> 01:32:48,700
It's just...

1020
01:32:53,570 --> 01:32:54,570
What is it?

1021
01:32:56,970 --> 01:32:58,570
Explain yourself.

1022
01:33:03,870 --> 01:33:09,070
Miu has had to go through so much on her own.

1023
01:33:10,930 --> 01:33:12,530
Came back pregnant.

1024
01:33:12,930 --> 01:33:14,330
Had a baby.

1025
01:33:14,670 --> 01:33:16,870
Worked like crazy while raising a kid.

1026
01:33:17,890 --> 01:33:19,500
Came back pregnant?

1027
01:33:22,070 --> 01:33:22,870
No!

1028
01:33:24,070 --> 01:33:26,930
Himari is mine.

1029
01:33:37,670 --> 01:33:38,930
Please leave.

1030
01:33:39,970 --> 01:33:41,070
I beg you.

1031
01:34:12,920 --> 01:34:15,130
Tamashiro Miu

1032
01:34:19,300 --> 01:34:22,130
The number you have dialled...

1033
01:34:25,400 --> 01:34:27,800
That looks so yummy.

1034
01:34:28,670 --> 01:34:30,070
Can I please have another?

1035
01:34:30,900 --> 01:34:31,930
What flavour is this?

1036
01:34:32,930 --> 01:34:34,000
- Soda.
- Soda?

1037
01:34:34,530 --> 01:34:35,330
One, two...

1038
01:34:36,600 --> 01:34:37,400
How's the taste?

1039
01:34:37,930 --> 01:34:38,600
Yummy.

1040
01:34:38,600 --> 01:34:39,400
Yummy?

1041
01:34:43,670 --> 01:34:46,970
Um, is Minato-senpai back yet?

1042
01:34:47,000 --> 01:34:49,900
Not yet it seems.

1043
01:34:53,770 --> 01:34:54,600
Are you alright?

1044
01:34:56,760 --> 01:34:58,480
Thanks for your help.

1045
01:35:33,020 --> 01:35:34,060
Miu.

1046
01:35:35,790 --> 01:35:36,670
Miu?

1047
01:35:41,580 --> 01:35:42,710
We're home.

1048
01:35:48,310 --> 01:35:49,380
Ryusei.

1049
01:35:50,050 --> 01:35:51,610
What's going on?

1050
01:35:53,850 --> 01:35:57,060
I will absolutely make you and Himari happy.

1051
01:36:07,590 --> 01:36:08,710
Himari.

1052
01:36:18,070 --> 01:36:20,370
This was Mom's favourite smell, wasn't it?

1053
01:36:21,670 --> 01:36:22,470
What?

1054
01:36:23,500 --> 01:36:27,000
It's your favourite, Minato.

1055
01:36:27,290 --> 01:36:27,870
Eh?

1056
01:36:27,870 --> 01:36:32,500
You were the one who said you like it, Minato.

1057
01:36:32,600 --> 01:36:34,340
So your mom, dad and I

1058
01:36:34,340 --> 01:36:36,700
surrounded the house with them.

1059
01:36:40,370 --> 01:36:44,170
You must never forget the things that you love.

1060
01:37:11,570 --> 01:37:12,310
Excuse me.

1061
01:37:12,310 --> 01:37:13,690
Can you please stop?

1062
01:37:42,200 --> 01:37:43,550
Thank you!

1063
01:37:44,450 --> 01:37:46,410
- Thank you!
- Congratulations!

1064
01:38:47,320 --> 01:38:49,890
What's wrong, Himari?

1065
01:38:52,390 --> 01:38:53,270
Miu?

1066
01:38:53,270 --> 01:38:54,430
Something the matter?

1067
01:38:54,530 --> 01:38:55,370
Himari...

1068
01:38:56,420 --> 01:38:57,780
What's the matter, Himari?

1069
01:38:57,960 --> 01:38:59,030
Let's go.

1070
01:39:53,260 --> 01:39:55,560
Tokyo

1071
01:40:05,300 --> 01:40:06,100
Himari.

1072
01:40:06,530 --> 01:40:07,500
Are you okay?

1073
01:40:24,110 --> 01:40:26,030
Hello, Himari.

1074
01:40:28,500 --> 01:40:29,330
Dad.

1075
01:40:31,040 --> 01:40:33,000
Did you meet Minato-senpai?

1076
01:40:35,300 --> 01:40:36,470
Is that man...

1077
01:40:39,530 --> 01:40:41,950
my real father?

1078
01:40:45,400 --> 01:40:46,370
Yes, he is.

1079
01:40:47,770 --> 01:40:51,070
How could you keep something like this from me?

1080
01:40:54,100 --> 01:40:56,530
We were going to tell you when you turned twenty.

1081
01:40:57,090 --> 01:40:58,700
It was a promise I made with your mother.

1082
01:41:01,610 --> 01:41:03,080
But your mother is...

1083
01:41:07,100 --> 01:41:07,860
That's why,

1084
01:41:08,780 --> 01:41:10,300
I want you and your mom,

1085
01:41:10,810 --> 01:41:13,200
and your real father to all meet.

1086
01:41:13,370 --> 01:41:14,980
How can you decide something like that?

1087
01:41:17,170 --> 01:41:20,730
You can't spring that on me and expect me to understand.

1088
01:41:24,700 --> 01:41:26,300
I don't want to see him.

1089
01:41:29,930 --> 01:41:30,730
Himari.

1090
01:41:32,900 --> 01:41:34,070
Where are you going?

1091
01:41:34,220 --> 01:41:35,670
Back home to Okinawa.

1092
01:41:37,680 --> 01:41:38,580
Wait.

1093
01:41:41,760 --> 01:41:43,280
What about your promise to your dad?

1094
01:41:43,280 --> 01:41:44,450
I don't care.

1095
01:41:45,700 --> 01:41:48,300
Don't tell me you know everything, Kotaro.

1096
01:41:49,770 --> 01:41:51,670
I don't know anything.

1097
01:41:53,320 --> 01:41:54,090
All I know.

1098
01:41:55,130 --> 01:41:57,870
Is that your dad is trying desperately.

1099
01:42:00,770 --> 01:42:01,430
But...

1100
01:42:01,430 --> 01:42:03,000
You should save your frustrations,

1101
01:42:04,930 --> 01:42:08,200
and tell your dad when you get home.

1102
01:42:11,440 --> 01:42:12,140
Alright?

1103
01:42:38,270 --> 01:42:39,180
This is it.

1104
01:42:45,730 --> 01:42:46,530
Alright.

1105
01:42:47,930 --> 01:42:49,000
C'mon, go.

1106
01:42:52,100 --> 01:42:53,770
You're coming right, Kotaro?

1107
01:42:54,170 --> 01:42:55,700
I'll wait here.

1108
01:43:00,970 --> 01:43:03,000
We're not kids anymore, are we?

1109
01:43:33,530 --> 01:43:34,700
What's the matter?

1110
01:43:47,910 --> 01:43:49,500
Mochizuki Kasumi?

1111
01:43:50,800 --> 01:43:51,990
No way.

1112
01:43:52,680 --> 01:43:55,350
Can you push the reverb a bit more on the guitar?

1113
01:43:55,870 --> 01:43:56,670
So you mean...

1114
01:43:57,770 --> 01:43:58,570
Minato.

1115
01:43:59,470 --> 01:44:00,330
You have a visitor.

1116
01:44:01,800 --> 01:44:03,600
Let's take a break and try it later.

1117
01:44:03,900 --> 01:44:04,870
Thanks.

1118
01:44:06,270 --> 01:44:08,130
- Good day.
- Good day.

1119
01:44:13,630 --> 01:44:14,300
Come in.

1120
01:44:27,800 --> 01:44:28,580
I'll leave you.

1121
01:44:28,820 --> 01:44:29,880
Take your time.

1122
01:44:31,460 --> 01:44:32,210
Huh?

1123
01:44:45,130 --> 01:44:46,020
You are...

1124
01:44:48,010 --> 01:44:49,420
Minato-san, right?

1125
01:44:51,640 --> 01:44:52,890
Yes, I am.

1126
01:45:05,600 --> 01:45:06,330
Here.

1127
01:45:17,770 --> 01:45:21,020
Please look at the label inside.

1128
01:45:28,930 --> 01:45:31,070
It's from my mom.

1129
01:45:38,000 --> 01:45:39,520
My mom's sick.

1130
01:45:44,000 --> 01:45:45,960
She might not make it.

1131
01:45:55,690 --> 01:45:57,050
Please listen to it.

1132
01:46:14,620 --> 01:46:16,440
It's the second track.

1133
01:46:29,380 --> 01:46:30,280
Minato.

1134
01:46:31,460 --> 01:46:32,400
How are you?

1135
01:46:38,130 --> 01:46:39,770
I'm doing well.

1136
01:46:44,330 --> 01:46:48,180
Actually, I'm getting married tomorrow.

1137
01:46:51,790 --> 01:46:52,570
You know.

1138
01:46:53,800 --> 01:46:57,300
I had a baby.

1139
01:46:59,860 --> 01:47:01,600
Her name is Himari.

1140
01:47:02,790 --> 01:47:04,300
Always cheerful

1141
01:47:04,930 --> 01:47:06,370
like a ray of sunshine.

1142
01:47:07,730 --> 01:47:09,870
She's my treasure.

1143
01:47:10,800 --> 01:47:11,600
Also,

1144
01:47:12,270 --> 01:47:14,600
I fulfilled my dream of becoming an interpreter.

1145
01:47:16,670 --> 01:47:18,570
My days are hectic but,

1146
01:47:19,330 --> 01:47:21,570
I'm living life without any regrets.

1147
01:47:25,500 --> 01:47:26,580
Hey, Minato.

1148
01:47:27,930 --> 01:47:31,220
Do you remember the first time we met?

1149
01:47:33,070 --> 01:47:36,900
You were going through a really tough time.

1150
01:47:37,270 --> 01:47:38,810
You were in so much pain.

1151
01:47:40,320 --> 01:47:44,000
That's why when I saw you smile for the very first time,

1152
01:47:44,930 --> 01:47:47,470
I remember feeling so happy.

1153
01:47:50,530 --> 01:47:54,930
When I realised that I always wanted to be by your side, to see you smile.

1154
01:47:57,290 --> 01:48:00,940
I think that's when I fell in love with you.

1155
01:48:04,190 --> 01:48:05,870
When we started dating.

1156
01:48:07,000 --> 01:48:09,470
Everyday was filled with joy.

1157
01:48:11,150 --> 01:48:13,780
Minato, if ever again,

1158
01:48:14,100 --> 01:48:17,200
you are going through pain and difficulties.

1159
01:48:18,670 --> 01:48:20,510
I want to protect you.

1160
01:48:22,100 --> 01:48:25,000
I want to make you happy, Minato.

1161
01:48:27,100 --> 01:48:28,670
That’s what I started thinking..

1162
01:48:30,710 --> 01:48:32,670
Since getting to know you, Minato.

1163
01:48:34,570 --> 01:48:36,160
The scent of those flowers,

1164
01:48:38,610 --> 01:48:40,870
the way you touch your nose when you're embarrassed,

1165
01:48:42,990 --> 01:48:44,800
the overwhelming joy,

1166
01:48:46,990 --> 01:48:48,200
the pain of heartbreak.

1167
01:48:51,660 --> 01:48:53,330
You gave me all of that.

1168
01:48:54,300 --> 01:48:56,800
These are the treasures of my life.

1169
01:49:02,000 --> 01:49:04,170
The one who brought sunshine to my life,

1170
01:49:05,400 --> 01:49:06,700
is you, Minato.

1171
01:49:12,000 --> 01:49:13,900
I'm glad I met you, Minato.

1172
01:49:16,600 --> 01:49:18,500
I hope the path you've chosen,

1173
01:49:19,500 --> 01:49:22,970
is filled with ever lasting happiness.

1174
01:49:27,200 --> 01:49:28,070
Thank you.

1175
01:49:29,470 --> 01:49:30,270
Minato.

1176
01:49:46,690 --> 01:49:54,700
I love loved you.

1177
01:50:03,900 --> 01:50:04,870
You're...

1178
01:50:08,720 --> 01:50:11,380
my real father, aren't you?

1179
01:50:16,600 --> 01:50:18,600
The man who raised you,

1180
01:50:21,870 --> 01:50:23,930
is your real father.

1181
01:50:37,310 --> 01:50:38,110
Hey.

1182
01:50:39,310 --> 01:50:41,500
Could you give this to your mother for me?

1183
01:50:42,440 --> 01:50:44,070
Tell her I'm sorry it's late.

1184
01:50:51,770 --> 01:50:54,300
Can you let me see that?

1185
01:51:01,580 --> 01:51:03,130
29th February.

1186
01:51:05,870 --> 01:51:06,670
It's the same day.

1187
01:51:11,230 --> 01:51:13,800
Are you really not going to see my mother?

1188
01:51:16,720 --> 01:51:18,800
You may never be able to see her again.

1189
01:51:25,590 --> 01:51:28,400
The person your mother wants by her side in her final moments,

1190
01:51:29,780 --> 01:51:30,870
is not me.

1191
01:51:34,120 --> 01:51:35,370
You better get home.

1192
01:52:48,470 --> 01:52:49,470
Where's Himari?

1193
01:52:53,600 --> 01:52:55,070
She went to Tokyo.

1194
01:52:56,710 --> 01:52:58,500
To meet Minato-senpai.

1195
01:53:00,190 --> 01:53:00,900
What?

1196
01:53:01,800 --> 01:53:06,270
I'm sure Himari will bring Minato-senpai back with her.

1197
01:53:08,870 --> 01:53:09,870
What do you mean?

1198
01:53:12,930 --> 01:53:17,700
I want the three of you,

1199
01:53:21,370 --> 01:53:25,270
you, Himari, and Minato-senpai,

1200
01:53:26,730 --> 01:53:28,700
to spend time together as a real family.

1201
01:53:31,350 --> 01:53:32,970
Why would you say something like that?

1202
01:53:38,440 --> 01:53:40,300
I did something terrible.

1203
01:53:44,470 --> 01:53:46,060
The day before our wedding.

1204
01:53:48,200 --> 01:53:51,100
You left an MD in the mailbox at Minato-senpai's home.

1205
01:53:52,900 --> 01:53:54,500
And I took it.

1206
01:53:57,250 --> 01:53:58,000
And so,

1207
01:53:58,890 --> 01:54:00,400
he never received it.

1208
01:54:02,130 --> 01:54:05,770
The MD you meant for Minato-senpai.

1209
01:54:13,720 --> 01:54:14,400
I'm sorry.

1210
01:54:20,500 --> 01:54:21,570
I was scared.

1211
01:54:23,800 --> 01:54:25,930
Of losing you and Himari.

1212
01:54:28,540 --> 01:54:29,570
I was so scared.

1213
01:54:44,900 --> 01:54:46,870
There's no need to apologise, Ryusei.

1214
01:54:49,570 --> 01:54:50,900
No need at all.

1215
01:54:56,900 --> 01:54:58,670
Ryusei, you've always been,

1216
01:55:00,680 --> 01:55:02,700
right by my side.

1217
01:55:06,900 --> 01:55:09,530
You brought me so much joy,

1218
01:55:17,270 --> 01:55:18,500
Thank you,

1219
01:55:20,930 --> 01:55:22,930
for always being by my side.

1220
01:55:28,440 --> 01:55:30,570
For being Himari's father,

1221
01:55:35,190 --> 01:55:37,070
for becoming a family,

1222
01:55:41,890 --> 01:55:43,300
I'm truly thankful.

1223
01:55:49,930 --> 01:55:51,260
You're the one

1224
01:55:54,170 --> 01:55:55,970
I want by my side to the very end.

1225
01:56:34,890 --> 01:56:35,730
Hey Mom.

1226
01:56:42,890 --> 01:56:44,470
I have something for you.

1227
01:56:48,730 --> 01:56:50,270
It's from Minato-senpai.

1228
01:56:55,430 --> 01:56:57,130
He says he's sorry it's late.

1229
01:57:29,050 --> 01:57:31,140
Himari!
